Package org.ejbca.ra

Class EnrollMakeNewRequestBean

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ejbca.ra.EnrollMakeNewRequestBean
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    public class EnrollMakeNewRequestBean
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Managed bean that backs up the enrollingmakenewrequest.xhtml page. DEVELOP NOTE: Since the page this bean backs up has pretty advanced dependencies for what should be rendered when, an unconventional pattern is used where getters will calculate their current value based on the current state of their dependencies. (The normal pattern would be that changes/actions should calculate and modify everything that is effected by this change. This would be harder to code and maintain since you have to think about all permutations that could potentially be affected down the line.)
    Version:
    $Id: EnrollMakeNewRequestBean.java 34396 2020-01-28 13:50:08Z samuellb $ TODO: Use CDI beans

      • getValidityHelpMessage

        public String getValidityHelpMessage()
        Creates a help message whose content depends on the current value of the 'Validity'-field. The help message reflects one of the following four (error) states:
        • The validity is empty
        • The validity is non-empty but cannot be parsed
        • The validity is a parsable date or time interval but exceeds the maximum validity specified by the certificate profile
        • The validity is valid (no error)
        Returns:
        String

        public boolean isRenderNonModifiableTemplatesRendered()
        Determines whether any non-modifiable (disabled) templates are rendered or exists as hidden. If the selectable items havn't been selected yet, false is returned to not confuse a hidden item with an unselected item (hence we check if an item is not rendered AND selected). Hidden templates occur if there's only one selection or if the option is restricted to the profile.

        true if there are hidden static template options or if hidden templates are already rendered
